			"body": "<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: summarize by coderabbit.ai -->\n<!-- walkthrough_start -->\n\n<details>\n<summary>📝 Walkthrough</summary>\n\n## Walkthrough\n\nThis pull request introduces a new editor mode selector dialog feature for the Joplin desktop application. It adds UI components for choosing between Rich Text and Markdown editor modes, integrates the dialog into the application's state management and dialog registry, includes startup logic to conditionally display the selector on first launch, and adds a new persistent setting to track selector visibility.\n\n## Changes\n\n|Cohort / File(s)|Summary|\n|---|---|\n|**Configuration files** <br> `.eslintignore`, `.gitignore`|Added editor mode selector component and startup files to ignore lists.|\n|**Editor mode selector components** <br> `packages/app-desktop/gui/EditorModeSelector.tsx`, `packages/app-desktop/gui/EditorModeSelectorDialog.tsx`|Created new React components: a styled radiogroup UI component for mode selection and a dialog wrapper component with helper functions for committing selections and dismissing the dialog.|\n|**Startup and initialization** <br> `packages/app-desktop/gui/editorModeSelectorStartup.ts`, `packages/app-desktop/gui/editorModeSelectorStartup.test.ts`|Added startup logic to conditionally open the editor mode selector dialog based on a persistent setting, with unit tests validating the conditional display behaviour.|\n|**Integration with app state and dialogs** <br> `packages/app-desktop/app.reducer.ts`, `packages/app-desktop/gui/Root.tsx`, `packages/app-desktop/gui/WindowCommandsAndDialogs/utils/appDialogs.tsx`|Registered new dialog name in enum, scheduled startup check in component lifecycle, and registered dialog renderer in the application's dialog registry.|\n|**Styling** <br> `packages/app-desktop/gui/styles/editor-mode-selector-dialog.scss`, `packages/app-desktop/gui/styles/index.scss`|Added modal dialog layout styling with responsive content sizing and imported new stylesheet.|\n|**Settings metadata** <br> `packages/lib/models/settings/builtInMetadata.ts`|Added new boolean setting `editor.modeSelectorShown` to track whether the selector has been displayed to the user.|\n\n## Sequence Diagram(s)\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant Root as Application Root\n    participant Startup as editorModeSelectorStartup\n    participant Settings as Settings\n    participant Dispatch as Action Dispatcher\n    participant Dialog as EditorModeSelector Dialog\n    participant User as User\n    participant Editor as Editor State\n\n    Root->>Startup: openEditorModeSelector(dispatch)\n    Startup->>Settings: Check editor.modeSelectorShown\n    alt Setting not shown yet\n        Startup->>Dispatch: dispatch(DIALOG_OPEN, 'editorModeSelector')\n        Dispatch->>Dialog: Render EditorModeSelectorDialog\n        Dialog->>User: Display mode selection UI\n        User->>Dialog: Select mode (markdown/richText)\n        Dialog->>Dispatch: commitEditorModeSelection(dispatch, mode)\n        Dispatch->>Editor: Update editor.view setting\n        Dispatch->>Settings: Set editor.modeSelectorShown = true\n        Dialog->>Dialog: Close dialog\n    else Setting already shown\n        Startup-->>Startup: Return without action\n    end\n```\n\n## Possibly related PRs\n\n- PR laurent22/joplin#14403: Both PRs modify `packages/lib/models/settings/builtInMetadata.ts`—the main PR adds the new `editor.modeSelectorShown` setting while the related PR reorganises existing editor-scoped settings.\n\n## Suggested labels\n\n`enhancement`, `desktop`, `editor`\n\n</details>\n\n<!-- walkthrough_end -->\n\n\n<!-- pre_merge_checks_walkthrough_start -->\n\n<details>\n<summary>🚥 Pre-merge checks | ✅ 2 | ❌ 2</summary>\n\n### ❌ Failed checks (1 error, 1 warning)\n\n|               Check name              | Status     | Explanation                                                                                               | Resolution                         